<TITLE> Bangladesh tracks tsunami risks </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 12 (bdnews24.com)  The food and disaster management ministry Wednesday revived its watch cell to track tsunami risks. Acting disaster management secretary Dhiraj Kumar Malakar has been leading the monitoring team. The ministry asked deputy commissioners of 17 districts in coastal zones to deal with the situation in the event of tsunami waves. Golam Kibria, spokesman for the monitoring cell, told bdnews24.com that people had been moved to safety from risky areas in the 17 districts. "Nobody is at risk now," he claimed. bdn
